# Cloudflare Workers Static Assets — files matched here are skipped on
# upload (CF has a 25 MiB per-file limit and 20k file limit).
#
# We skip the vendored DuckDB-wasm fallback (~75 MB of WASM + workers)
# because (a) the eh.wasm + mvp.wasm files are 34 MB and 39 MB — both
# blow past the 25 MiB ceiling, and (b) the engine's CDN-load path
# fetches the same bytes from jsDelivr with version pinning. On
# Cloudflare deploys, NakliData falls back to the CDN path
# automatically (see src/main.ts boot — the HEAD probe of
# duckdb-fallback/integrity.json returns 404 here, so the runtime
# picks CDN-load).
#
# On GitHub Pages (which has a 100 MB per-file limit), the same
# directory ships fine — the HEAD probe returns 200 and the runtime
# uses the same-origin vendored bytes.
duckdb-fallback/
